Package cosmic_conquistadors

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Critter
    The Critter interface defines what methods on-screen objects should have.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Angle
    The Angle class represents an angle measured from the horizontal.
    Brigade  
    Config
    The Config class provides a way to save user settings to the hard drive and read it again when the program is restarted.
    DefaultCritter
    The DefaultCritter is the default implementation of the Critter interface.
    Encryption
    The Encryption class provides basic XOR encryption and decryption methods.
    Enemy
    The Enemy class is used to represent the evil aliens that are firing missiles at our hero as they ascend down to Earth.
    Hitbox
    The Hitbox class represents a box which is used for collision testing.
    InvaderGameState
    The InvaderGameState class is where the state of the game is managed along with the game loop and game logic.
    Invaders
    The Invaders class provides the entry point of the game where it loads the game settings and starts the game loop.
    Missile
    The Missile class is used to represent missiles fired by either the hero or enemies
    Shooter
    The Shooter class is used to represent our so-called hero that sits at the bottom of the screen and shoots missiles at oncoming enemies.
    Utility
    The Utility class provides utility methods which can be useful anywhere in the game.
    Vector
    The Vector class provides a way to represent values with both scale and magnitude in two dimensions.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ConfigFileNotFoundException
    The ConfigFileNotFoundException is signaled when there was an attempt to read/write from/to a Config file, but failed because the file does not exist.
    ConfigParseException
    The ConfigParseException is signaled when the parsing of a Config file failed because its syntax is ill-formed.
